  1. Information We Collect
    1.1 Google Sign-In Information
      When you sign in with Google, we receive only the following information:
        Email address
        Given name (Based on Google Account information)
        Google account ID (for authentication only)
    1.2 Display Name
        Your given name is used to generate a display name, which you may change.
    1.3 Automatically Collected Data
        Cipher Yield itself does not collect additional personal information such as location, device identifiers, or analytics data outside of what is required 
            by third-party services you explicitly interact with, such as Google AdMob (see Section 7).
 
  2. How We Use Your Information
    We use your information to:
      Create and maintain your account
      Authenticate you securely
      Provide a display name
      Improve or maintain app functionality
      We do not sell or rent your data.

  3. Legal Bases for Processing (GDPR Requirement)
    For users located in the EU/UK, we process your data using these lawful bases:
      Performance of a Contract: We must process your email and Google ID to create and maintain your account.
      Legitimate Interest: To secure the Service and prevent misuse.
      Consent: For personalized ads delivered by Google AdMob (where required).
    You may withdraw consent for personalized ads at any time (details in Section 7).

  4. Your Rights (GDPR + CCPA)
    You have the right to:
      Access the data we hold about you
      Correct inaccurate information
      Delete your account and all associated data
      Export your data in a portable format (GDPR “Data Portability”)
      Request details about categories of data collected (CCPA)
      Opt out of data sale (we do not sell data, but we still honor this right)

    To exercise any rights, email: Alex.Vigested@gmail.com

  5. Non-Discrimination Statement (CCPA Requirement)
    We will not deny features, charge different prices, or provide lower-quality service because you exercised your privacy rights.

  6. Data Retention
    We keep account data only while your account remains active.
    Upon deletion, your personal data is removed or anonymized except where legally required.

  7. Third-Party Services — Google AdMob
    Cipher Yield uses Google AdMob to display advertisements, including reward-based ads.
      7.1 Information AdMob May Collect
        Google AdMob may automatically collect:
          Advertising identifiers (e.g., AAID)
          IP address
          Device information
          Interaction with ads
          Approximate location
          App usage analytics
          Data needed to show personalized or non-personalized ads
        This collection is governed by Google’s own Privacy & Terms, not Cipher Yield.
      7.2 Consent for Personalized Ads (GDPR & EU Users)

Users in the EU/UK must be presented with a consent form before personalized ads are shown.
You must:

Ask users if they want personalized ads

Allow users to decline

Store the consent decision

Allow the user to change their choice

7.3 Opt-Out for U.S. Users

Users in the United States may opt out of:

Interest-based advertising

“Sale” or “sharing” of data for advertising (under California CPRA)

Cipher Yield will honor system-level “opt out of ads personalization” where applicable.

7.4 Children’s Ads (COPPA)

Cipher Yield is not intended for children under 13.
AdMob must be configured in:

non-child mode

not directed toward children

8. Data Sharing

We share data only as necessary for:

Account authentication (Google)

Advertising (AdMob)

We do not share your information with third parties for marketing purposes.

9. Security

We use reasonable administrative and technical measures to protect data.
However, no method is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute protection.

10. Changes to This Policy

We may update this policy. The updated date will reflect the latest revision.

11. Contact Us

For privacy questions or requests:

